Just saw Doctor Strange in the Multiverse of Madness, and what a movie it was. I'll be giving my thoughts on it in this thread. Be warned, spoilers follow!

To start off, I'll just say that this movie was better than I expected it to be. I honestly thought that this movie was just going to end up being a mess of multiverses and a lot of wasted potential. And while it was quite the mess of multiverses, it didn't waste its potential.
@juicewtt @xdivinedoll Captain America isn’t British so he’s stronger and would win

Also, I love what they did with Wanda. It seemed out of character and kind of absurd and points what she did and her logic for doing it. Yet it was still awesome to see the Scarlet Witch in action and hungry for blood. She's definitely one of my favorite Marvel characters...

Now for the cameos. I think the Illuminati was a nice touch to the film, even though none of them really did much in the movie. John Krasinski as Mister Fantastic was perfect, as we all knew he would be. He personified that character extremely well and left me wanting to see more

...and Elizabeth Olsen plays her tremendously every single time. Considering it was a sequel to Doctor Strange and Wandavision, I think it did a good job giving both some good screen time as well as development.

Overall the movie was great. Sam Raimi did a good job keeping things relatively under control in a wild movie such as this. There were lots of small visual touches that were great too. I would definitely recommend seeing this movie to anyone who's a Marvel fan.

Sharon Carter as Captain America was a cool way to tie in the What If... series to the actual movies, and the role of Mordo in this film was also very interesting, though it did leave the question of where's the Mordo in Strange's normal universe.
